<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-31T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-31T14:00:00-05:00" n="817" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 637.119/479</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GWE1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-31T15:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your July 17, 10 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d817fn1">Not printed.</note>
                            Department regrets that an old agreement obligates us to give coal for
                            the customary schedule of the steamers of the Compañía Transatlántica.
                            This does not, however, apply to other Spanish steamers on which it is
                            the intention of the War Trade Board to furnish coal only so far as
                            Cuban ports leaving the question of any further extension of the voyages
                            in the hands of the Cuban authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>